"613","Report of Independent Registered Public Accounting"
"614","Firm"
"615","To the Trustees of DWS Investment Trust and the"
"616","Shareholders of DWS S&P 500 Index Fund:"
"617","In planning and performing our audit of the financial"
"618","statements of DWS S&P 500 Index Fund (the"
"619","Fund), as of and for the year ended December 31,"
"620","2009, in accordance with the standards of the Public"
"621","Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States), we"
"622","considered the Fund's internal control over"
"623","financial reporting, including control activities for"
"624","safeguarding securities, as a basis for designing our"
"625","auditing procedures for the purpose of expressing our"
"626","opinion on the financial statements and to comply"
"627","with the requirements of Form N-SAR, but not for the"
"628","purpose of expressing an opinion on the"
"629","effectiveness of the Fund's internal control over"
"630","financial reporting.  Accordingly, we do not express"
"631","an"
"632","opinion on the effectiveness of the Fund's internal"
"633","control over financial reporting."
"634","The management of the Fund is responsible for"
"635","establishing and maintaining effective internal"
"636","control"
"637","over financial reporting.  In fulfilling this"
"638","responsibility, estimates and judgments by management"
"639","are"
"640","required to assess the expected benefits and related"
"641","costs of controls.  A fund's internal control over"
"642","financial reporting is a process designed to provide"
"643","reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of"
"644","financial reporting and the preparation of financial"
"645","statements for external purposes in accordance with"
"646","generally accepted accounting principles.  A fund's"
"647","internal control over financial reporting includes"
"648","those"
"649","policies and procedures that (1) pertain to the"
"650","maintenance of records that, in reasonable detail,"
"651","accurately and fairly reflect the transactions and"
"652","dispositions of the assets of the fund; (2) provide"
"653","reasonable assurance that transactions are recorded as"
"654","necessary to permit preparation of financial"
"655","statements in accordance with generally accepted"
"656","accounting principles, and that receipts and"
"657","expenditures of the fund are being made only in"
"658","accordance with authorizations of management and"
"659","trustees of the fund; and (3)  provide reasonable"
"660","assurance regarding prevention or timely detection of"
"661","unauthorized acquisition, use or disposition of a"
"662","fund's assets that could have a material effect on the"
"663","financial statements."
"664","Because of its inherent limitations, internal control"
"665","over financial reporting may not prevent or detect"
"666","misstatements. Also, projections of any evaluation of"
"667","effectiveness to future periods are subject to the"
"668","risk"
"669","that controls may become inadequate because of changes"
"670","in conditions, or that the degree of compliance"
"671","with the policies or procedures may deteriorate."
"672","A deficiency in internal control over financial"
"673","reporting exists when the design or operation of a"
"674","control"
"675","does not allow management or employees, in the normal"
"676","course of performing their assigned functions,"
"677","to prevent or detect misstatements on a timely basis."
"678","A material weakness is a deficiency, or a"
"679","combination of deficiencies, in internal control over"
"680","financial reporting, such that there is a reasonable"
"681","possibility that a material misstatement of the Fund's"
"682","annual or interim financial statements will not be"
"683","prevented or detected on a timely basis."
"684","Our consideration of the Fund's internal control over"
"685","financial reporting was for the limited purpose"
"686","described in the first paragraph and would not"
"687","necessarily disclose all deficiencies in internal"
"688","control over"
"689","financial reporting that might be material weaknesses"
"690","under standards established by the Public"
"691","Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States)."
"692","However, we noted no deficiencies in the Fund's"
"693","internal control over financial reporting and its"
"694","operation, including controls for safeguarding"
"695","securities,"
"696","that we consider to be material weaknesses as defined"
"697","above as of December 31, 2009."
"698","This report is intended solely for the information and"
"699","use of the Trustees, management, and the"
"700","Securities and Exchange Commission and is not intended"
"701","to be and should not be used by anyone other"
"702","than these specified parties."
"703","PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP"
"704","February 26, 2010"
